00:08:40.549 --> 00:08:50.000 align:middle line:84%
>> This is my story, impromptu
story of how I've come to find

00:08:50.000 --> 00:08:58.370 align:middle line:84%
a way out a day at a time
from compulsive overeating

00:08:58.370 --> 00:09:00.290 align:middle line:90%
and obesity.

00:09:00.290 --> 00:09:07.310 align:middle line:84%
I grew up watching my mom, who
was an obese woman, struggle

00:09:07.310 --> 00:09:10.020 align:middle line:90%
to overcome it.

00:09:10.020 --> 00:09:12.870 align:middle line:84%
And I watched her when
I was a little girl.

00:09:12.870 --> 00:09:14.990 align:middle line:84%
I remember when I
was five years old

00:09:14.990 --> 00:09:19.160 align:middle line:84%
having to hold her hand
while she walked to work down

00:09:19.160 --> 00:09:23.030 align:middle line:84%
the block at the
hospital because she was

00:09:23.030 --> 00:09:25.100 align:middle line:90%
so big she couldn't balance.

00:09:25.100 --> 00:09:26.990 align:middle line:84%
She had difficulty
balancing her body,

00:09:26.990 --> 00:09:30.320 align:middle line:84%
and she was afraid she
would slip on the ice.

00:09:30.320 --> 00:09:33.650 align:middle line:84%
She had varicose veins
that made it difficult

00:09:33.650 --> 00:09:36.170 align:middle line:90%
for her to walk and stand.

00:09:36.170 --> 00:09:39.680 align:middle line:84%
And I remember
seeing her hide food

00:09:39.680 --> 00:09:43.580 align:middle line:90%
in drawers and in the hamper.

00:09:43.580 --> 00:09:50.210 align:middle line:84%
And I learned from
her how to deal

00:09:50.210 --> 00:09:54.470 align:middle line:84%
or attempt to deal and cope
with feelings by using food

00:09:54.470 --> 00:09:57.500 align:middle line:90%
as a drug.

00:09:57.500 --> 00:10:03.890 align:middle line:84%
When I was 27 years
old, my mother was 62,

00:10:03.890 --> 00:10:10.250 align:middle line:84%
and she retired from
work and got cancer.

00:10:10.250 --> 00:10:14.540 align:middle line:84%
And she was dead within
a year and a half.

00:10:14.540 --> 00:10:17.000 align:middle line:90%
They called the disease cancer.

00:10:17.000 --> 00:10:20.630 align:middle line:84%
I called it
compulsive overeating.

00:10:20.630 --> 00:10:22.640 align:middle line:90%
She was a grossly obese woman.

00:10:22.640 --> 00:10:25.670 align:middle line:90%


00:10:25.670 --> 00:10:31.640 align:middle line:84%
She had no skills
for coping with life.

00:10:31.640 --> 00:10:34.910 align:middle line:84%
And I guess the combination
of growing up and watching

00:10:34.910 --> 00:10:41.510 align:middle line:84%
her struggle and never learning
how to love or accept herself

00:10:41.510 --> 00:10:46.370 align:middle line:84%
and then seeing her die was
tremendous motivation for me

00:10:46.370 --> 00:10:48.740 align:middle line:90%
to overcome this problem.

00:10:48.740 --> 00:10:52.910 align:middle line:84%
I was really determined to
find a way out for myself.

00:10:52.910 --> 00:10:56.160 align:middle line:90%
