00:10:56.160 --> 00:10:59.450 align:middle line:84%
I went to all different
major corporations,

00:10:59.450 --> 00:11:03.300 align:middle line:84%
you know, Weight Watchers and
Think Thin and Way of Life

00:11:03.300 --> 00:11:07.460 align:middle line:84%
and just tried every
kind of diet program

00:11:07.460 --> 00:11:08.750 align:middle line:90%
imaginable out there.

00:11:08.750 --> 00:11:12.650 align:middle line:90%
And it wasn't the answer.

00:11:12.650 --> 00:11:14.810 align:middle line:84%
I was introduced
to a program called

00:11:14.810 --> 00:11:18.410 align:middle line:84%
Overeaters Anonymous,
where I learned that this

00:11:18.410 --> 00:11:20.990 align:middle line:90%
was a threefold illness--

00:11:20.990 --> 00:11:25.310 align:middle line:84%
spiritual, emotional,
and physical.

00:11:25.310 --> 00:11:31.010 align:middle line:84%
And that's where my
path began on the road

00:11:31.010 --> 00:11:34.950 align:middle line:84%
to heal physically,
emotionally, and spiritually.

00:11:34.950 --> 00:11:38.840 align:middle line:84%
Emotionally I had to
learn and am still working

00:11:38.840 --> 00:11:42.110 align:middle line:90%
on loving and accepting myself.

00:11:42.110 --> 00:11:44.330 align:middle line:84%
The emotional
recovery took being

00:11:44.330 --> 00:11:51.200 align:middle line:84%
able to look at and be with all
of the emotions, the dark side

00:11:51.200 --> 00:11:57.740 align:middle line:84%
of me, the shadow self, as
one famous therapist calls it.

00:11:57.740 --> 00:12:01.310 align:middle line:84%
I had to be able to look
at and be with myself

00:12:01.310 --> 00:12:07.130 align:middle line:84%
when I felt jealous,
when I felt angry,

00:12:07.130 --> 00:12:10.460 align:middle line:84%
when I was judgmental
of other people.

00:12:10.460 --> 00:12:13.220 align:middle line:84%
And I had to be able to
stay present with that

00:12:13.220 --> 00:12:19.430 align:middle line:84%
and ride those feelings
and not turn to food

00:12:19.430 --> 00:12:25.560 align:middle line:84%
to bury them as I
had my whole life.

00:12:25.560 --> 00:12:30.710 align:middle line:84%
It took some courage and
willpower in that way.

00:12:30.710 --> 00:12:37.370 align:middle line:84%
And I found that prayer
was and continues

00:12:37.370 --> 00:12:41.540 align:middle line:90%
to be an essential tool for me.

00:12:41.540 --> 00:12:46.890 align:middle line:84%
I learned that prayer was
an extremely powerful tool.

00:12:46.890 --> 00:12:50.300 align:middle line:84%
I had a difficult time
with it for many years.

00:12:50.300 --> 00:13:00.690 align:middle line:84%
I thought of God or the higher
power as a punishing force.

00:13:00.690 --> 00:13:05.280 align:middle line:84%
I sort of transferred my
experience with my dad

00:13:05.280 --> 00:13:08.770 align:middle line:84%
into this concept
of a higher power.

00:13:08.770 --> 00:13:13.140 align:middle line:84%
So I couldn't imagine
some force that

00:13:13.140 --> 00:13:17.100 align:middle line:84%
was compassionate
beyond comprehension,

00:13:17.100 --> 00:13:20.490 align:middle line:84%
that was loving beyond
comprehension, that

00:13:20.490 --> 00:13:24.990 align:middle line:84%
was merciful beyond
my comprehension,

00:13:24.990 --> 00:13:28.410 align:middle line:84%
